org.rsna.ctp.pipeline

Class AbstractQueuedExportService

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rsna.ctp.pipeline.AbstractPipelineStage
      • org.rsna.ctp.pipeline.AbstractQueuedExportService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExportService, PipelineStage, Scriptable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractExportService, DatabaseExportService, PolledHttpExportService

    public abstract class AbstractQueuedExportService
extends AbstractPipelineStage
implements ExportService, Scriptable
    An abstract class implementing the ExportService interface. This class provides the queue management and status functions so ExportServices only have to receive files and add them to the queue directory.

      • export

        public void export(FileObject fileObject)
        Add a FileObject to the export queue if the ExportService is configured to accept the FileObject class or subclass. If a script file corresponding to the object is defined, compute its value and enqueue the object if the result is true. This method enqueues the object and returns immediately.
        Specified by:
        export in interface ExportService
        Parameters:
        fileObject - the object to be exported.

      • getQueueSize

      • recount

        protected int recount()
        Force a recount of the export queue. return the size of the export queue, or 0 if no QueueManager exists.

      • getNextFile

        protected java.io.File getNextFile()
        Get the next file in the queue for exporting. This method moves the file to the active directory. Note that this means that if the export fails in such a way that a retry is appropriate, the file must be requeued.

      • release

        protected boolean release(java.io.File file)
        Release a file from the active directory. Note that the file may have moved, so it is possible that the file will no longer exist. This method only deletes the file if it is still in the active directory.
        Parameters:
        file - the file to be released, which must be the original file supplied by the ExportService.
